The paper deals with lower bounds on matrix multiplication algorithms, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on the Universal method and its limitations on various tensors, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of various degenerations of tensors, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of Strassen's Laser method also involves information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
